        "subject": "LU-18687 compat: use unexported vfree_atomic in kernel",
        "message": "LU-18687 compat: use unexported vfree_atomic in kernel\n\nWith the removal of RHEL7 support we can drop the special\nvfree_atomic() implementation we have. Instead just use\ncfs_kallsym_lookup to use vfree_atomic() that is available\nin modern kernels.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nChange-Id: I1cff923eda6a7b6df8db81477b9cd507416fb825\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61414\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
